{"cursor":"3429","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Mithila Prasad Tripathi' is a Sanskrit poet who won the Sahitya Akademi Award\nfor Sanskrit for 2010 for his poetry. The Sahitya Akademi is\nIndia's national academy of letters that awards the Jnanpith Award, India's\nhighest literary award, and the Sahitya Akademi Award for each language is\nconsidered the second-highest literary award in India and the highest award for\nthat language.\n\nHe was the director of Kalidasa Akademi in Ujjain from 2007 to\n2010. [http://ujjain.nic.in/kalidasa_academi/kalidasa_academi.htm Kalidasa\nAkademi] [http://www.kalidasaakademi.nic.in/Kalidas_Akademy/body_kali-\ndas_akademy.html Kalidasa Akademi] He is also the chairman of Maharshi\nPatanjali Sanskrit Pratishthan, Bhopal, and was on the advisory board of the\nWorld Samskrit Book Fair held in January 2010. [http://www.organiser.org/dy-\nnamic/modules.php?name=Content&pa=showpage&pid=345&page=30 Advisory Board for\nInternational Sanskrit Book Fair announced] [http://www.samskritbookfair.org/about/national-advisory-\nboard World Samskrit Book Fair] Additionally, he has served on the Madhya\nPradesh Sanskrit Board [http://www.sednmp.nic.in/Telephone.htm#11 Department\nof School Education, MP] and on the Board of Management of the Rashtriya\nSanskrit Sansthan. [http://www.sanskrit.nic.in/annual_report/2008_09/03.pdf\nRashtriya Sanskrit Sansthan Annual Report 2008â09]\n","linknr":120,"url":"Mithila_Prasad_Tripathi","recorded":1375084399,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Mithila_Prasad_Tripathi&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Mithila_Prasad_Tripathi&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccharinsert%2Cteahouse%7Cext.rtlcite%2